OL,6,FA critical incident is usually
OL,7,Fdeclared when a health board is
OL,8,Fstruggling to cope with unprecedented
OL,9,Fdemand. It can also be used to
OL,10,Fdescribe an event which could cause
OL,11,Fserious harm the health or welfare of
OL,12,Fthe patient.
OL,14,FPaul Mears, chief executive of Cwm Taf
OL,15,FMorgannwg University Health Board,
OL,16,Fsaid: "The safety of our staff and
OL,17,Fpatients on site remains our top
OL,18,Fpriority, and we are taking immediate
OL,19,Faction to bring the roof, which is
OL,20,Fmore the 40 years old, up to an
OL,21,Facceptable and modern standard.
